      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "[La26] C. F. Lau, On the number of prime factors of consecutive integers. arXiv:2604.15042 (2026)."
    },
    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "c4da16459746bb3c2a3c95d479e833980a1ee942edd98a0a028164409f49cef3",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A stronger form of [248].\n\nLau \\cite{La26} has proved that there exists an absolute constant $C$ such that, for infinitely many $n$,\\[\\tau(n+k) \\ll k^C\\]for all $k\\geq 1$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "caa7760648c6f49646e34ed6a9a6458b3d3a82c1d655219b1039bf2618e6d211",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Are there infinitely many $n$ such that, for all $k\\geq 1$,\\[\\tau(n+k)\\ll k?\\]"
    }
  },
